Despite the preceding provisions, the Broker Dealer will only be responsible for indemnifying and providing protection against harm to Distributor and Issuer if such responsibility arises from circumstances that do not involve negligence, misconduct, or wrongful acts by the Broker Dealer or its producer. This exemption applies when these actions are related to any untrue statement or alleged untrue statement of material fact, or the omission or alleged omission of a material fact in:

(i) any registration statement, including any prospectus or any post -effective amendment thereto;
(ii) any material prepared and/or supplied by Distributor or Issuer for use in conjunction with the offer or sale of Annuity Contracts;
(iii) any state registration or other document filed in any state or jurisdiction in order to qualify any Annuity Contracts under the securities laws of such state or jurisdiction.

In contrast, with regard to the solicitation of applications for the purchase of Annuity Contracts, Distributor and Issuer shall indemnify and hold harmless the Broker Dealer from any damage or expense, including reasonable attorneys' fees, resulting from negligence, misconduct, or wrongful acts by them, their employees, representatives, or agents. This protection extends to situations involving untrue statements or alleged untrue statements of material fact, omissions or alleged omissions of material facts, and any actual or alleged violations of securities or insurance laws, regulations, or orders.

The provisions of this section will persist even after the termination of this Agreement.
